 @MathiasKandelborg  I understand you are upset but we could do without the `extremely unorthodox behavior` or thumbs down :) 

Contrary to vim, neovim enables autoread by default and thanks to our gsoc student @BK1603  neovim reloads changed files on Focus events (unlike vim where autoread is most effective in gvim actually) and the #12593 is also his work so the problem is being addressed (Actually we are looking for feedback on that PR).
The help for autoread is misleading IMO since it does'nt mention the requirements/tricks but we inherited it from vim.
